  "prompt": "What are the must watch Hollywood movies before you die (count not more than 10)?",
  "response": "Here\u2019s a curated list of 10 must-watch Hollywood movies that are widely regarded as cinematic masterpieces, spanning various genres and eras. These films have left an indelible mark on cinema and are essential viewing for any film enthusiast:\n\n1. **The Godfather (1972)** - Francis Ford Coppola\u2019s epic crime saga about power, family, and loyalty in the mafia world.\n\n2. **Citizen Kane (1941)** - Orson Welles' groundbreaking film that redefined storytelling and cinematography in cinema.\n\n3. **Schindler\u2019s List (1993)** - Steven Spielberg\u2019s harrowing yet profound account of the Holocaust and one man\u2019s efforts to save lives.\n\n4. **Casablanca (1942)** - A timeless romantic drama set during WWII, starring Humphrey Bogart and Ingrid Bergman.\n\n5. **The Shawshank Redemption (1994)** - A powerful tale of hope and friendship set in a prison, based on a Stephen King novella.\n\n6. **2001: A Space Odyssey (1968)** - Stanley Kubrick\u2019s visionary sci-fi film exploring humanity\u2019s place in the universe.\n\n7. **Pulp Fiction (1994)** - Quentin Tarantino\u2019s groundbreaking nonlinear narrative and darkly comedic crime story.\n\n8. **Gone with the Wind (1939)** - A sweeping epic set during the American Civil War, known for its romance and historical backdrop.\n\n9. **Star Wars: Episode IV - A New Hope (1977)** - George Lucas\u2019 space opera that revolutionized the sci-fi genre and pop culture.\n\n10. **Titanic (1997)** - James Cameron\u2019s epic romance and disaster film based on the tragic sinking of the RMS Titanic.\n\nThese films are celebrated for their storytelling, direction, performances, and cultural impact, making them essential viewing for anyone who loves cinema.",
